## Proposed Solution: 3-Phase Fix

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Phase 1** (pipeline logic fixes) can be done immediately on your local machine.  
> **Phase 2** (retrain M1 + M2) requires Google Colab with GPU.  
> **Phase 3** (new M4 collision-zone detector) requires Colab GPU and is the biggest accuracy improvement.

### Phase 1: Pipeline Logic Fixes (Local, No Training)

Fix the code bugs and over-aggressive fallbacks that cause false positives even with the current models.

### Phase 2: Retrain M1 + M2 with Better Data (Colab GPU)

- **M1**: Add hard negatives (busy Indian traffic scenes) to training
- **M2**: Completely overhaul with Indian vehicle images as "normal" class; use ONLY close-up crash photos as "damaged"

### Phase 3: New M4 Collision-Zone Detector (Colab GPU)

Instead of trying to infer which vehicles collided from geometric heuristics, train a model that **directly detects the collision zone** in a frame. This is the fundamental paradigm shift:

**Current approach:** Detect vehicles → Figure out which ones collided (fragile)  
**New approach:** Detect the collision directly → Find vehicles inside it (robust)

